## 5. Psych‑Risk and NEU Exposure Budgets

5.1 Any HCI episode with non‑trivial psych‑risk (e.g., high‑stakes XR, intense adversarial games, identity‑altering upgrades) MUST consume a Neuro‑Risk Exposure Unit (NEU) budget, with NEU treated as a non‑transferable, auto‑mint/auto‑burn scalar per User. [ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws](https://ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws.com/web/direct-files/collection_e4057470-7756-497e-a75f-b79d6abfc921/f4728f17-d461-4b2e-85b9-ca6ecc397c0b/text-path-jurisdiction-policy-P2iE_lPMSR65ol_du7Gc4A.md)

5.2 NEU MAY NOT be bought, sold, delegated, or pooled. It is minted only from prosocial, clinically beneficial actions (rehab compliance, safety audits, governance work) and auto‑burned when risk‑bearing episodes occur. [ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws](https://ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws.com/web/direct-files/collection_e4057470-7756-497e-a75f-b79d6abfc921/f4728f17-d461-4b2e-85b9-ca6ecc397c0b/text-path-jurisdiction-policy-P2iE_lPMSR65ol_du7Gc4A.md)

5.3 Psych‑risk score \(R_e\) for an episode MUST be computed from intensity, novelty/complexity, and vulnerability, and NEU burn MUST satisfy ledger rules that prevent cumulative psych‑risk from crossing clinically derived safety bounds, independent of User risk‑seeking preferences. [ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws](https://ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws.com/web/direct-files/collection_e4057470-7756-497e-a75f-b79d6abfc921/f4728f17-d461-4b2e-85b9-ca6ecc397c0b/text-path-jurisdiction-policy-P2iE_lPMSR65ol_du7Gc4A.md)

5.4 Blood/protein tokens (e.g., CSP) MUST NOT directly mint NEU, to prevent coercive trades of psych‑risk for biological contribution. [ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws](https://ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws.com/web/direct-files/collection_e4057470-7756-497e-a75f-b79d6abfc921/f4728f17-d461-4b2e-85b9-ca6ecc397c0b/text-path-jurisdiction-policy-P2iE_lPMSR65ol_du7Gc4A.md)

