## 6. Safety Envelopes and Viability Kernels

6.1 The HCI MUST maintain a multi‑dimensional state representation of the User (including intensity, duty‑cycle, cumulative load, implant power, neuromod amplitude, cognitive load, legal complexity) and confine evolution to proved‑safe viability kernels per mode. [ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws](https://ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws.com/web/direct-files/collection_e4057470-7756-497e-a75f-b79d6abfc921/6352004e-65ab-4178-a76c-daeada0a3ebd/how-can-we-improve-cyber-retri-RVMuDeu7SuC4x52cE9Qhyw.md)

6.2 Any proposed control action MUST pass, in order:  
- A hardware/physics compliance gate (e.g., density, energy, coverage);  
- A bio‑safety envelope check (e.g., HRV, VO2, tissue limits);  
- A mode‑specific viability kernel check (next state remains inside kernel). [ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws](https://ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws.com/web/direct-files/collection_e4057470-7756-497e-a75f-b79d6abfc921/6352004e-65ab-4178-a76c-daeada0a3ebd/how-can-we-improve-cyber-retri-RVMuDeu7SuC4x52cE9Qhyw.md)

6.3 If any check fails, the action MUST be clipped, projected to the safe boundary, or rejected, and the event logged for audit.

***

## 7. Rights Kernel and Downgrade Resistance

7.1 A Rights Kernel MUST sit above all HCI policies, enforcing non‑negotiable floors (minimum capability, rollback strength, observability) and ceilings (max burden without explicit consent, max psych‑risk, max eco‑stress). [ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws](https://ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws.com/web/direct-files/collection_e4057470-7756-497e-a75f-b79d6abfc921/6352004e-65ab-4178-a76c-daeada0a3ebd/how-can-we-improve-cyber-retri-RVMuDeu7SuC4x52cE9Qhyw.md)

7.2 No update, CI pipeline, or policy may silently reduce User rights or capabilities; rights changes MUST be monotone (maintain or strengthen rights) and require explicit, time‑recent User consent. [ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws](https://ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws.com/web/direct-files/collection_e4057470-7756-497e-a75f-b79d6abfc921/34ee0756-6c1e-44b1-8218-ec28ea40e673/useful-knowledge-that-we-can-c-906f_S6ySTqZyZ1VK8GmTw.md)

7.3 A downgrade‑resistance shard (e.g., EibonSovereignContinuityV1) MUST log any attempt to narrow envelopes or rights, producing a cryptographic, tamper‑evident history of capability changes. [ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws](https://ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws.com/web/direct-files/collection_e4057470-7756-497e-a75f-b79d6abfc921/6352004e-65ab-4178-a76c-daeada0a3ebd/how-can-we-improve-cyber-retri-RVMuDeu7SuC4x52cE9Qhyw.md)

