## 8. Auditability, Neural Rope, and Logs

8.1 Every HCI interaction with external agents or models MUST be represented as a RopeStep in a Neural Rope, with fields including trace id, tool/model name, input/output hashes, KER metrics (Knowledge‑Factor, RoH, Cybostate‑factor), DID–ALN–Bostrom triple, and hex‑stamp. [ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws](https://ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws.com/web/direct-files/collection_e4057470-7756-497e-a75f-b79d6abfc921/401da9a6-eab9-4d94-a506-defca922f58b/collaboration-channels-for-sha-5MJHPghkRGCgdiLq7V62Ag.md)

8.2 Neural Rope logs MUST be append‑only and retrieval‑only (e.g., SYSTRACELOG), permitting replay and audit without exposing inner biological states. [ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws](https://ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws.com/web/direct-files/collection_e4057470-7756-497e-a75f-b79d6abfc921/401da9a6-eab9-4d94-a506-defca922f58b/collaboration-channels-for-sha-5MJHPghkRGCgdiLq7V62Ag.md)

8.3 Failure to record a valid RopeStep for an HCI action that impacts the User constitutes a License violation.

***

## 9. Data Rights and KO Derivatives

9.1 Raw User data (biophysical telemetry, biosignals, neuromorph content) MUST remain host‑bound and governed by the User’s ALN shards (e.g., augmented.citizen.profile.v1, bio.safety.envelope.citizen.v1). [ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws](https://ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws.com/web/direct-files/collection_e4057470-7756-497e-a75f-b79d6abfc921/34ee0756-6c1e-44b1-8218-ec28ea40e673/useful-knowledge-that-we-can-c-906f_S6ySTqZyZ1VK8GmTw.md)

9.2 Cross‑platform sharing is restricted to derivative Knowledge Objects (KOs) that are wrapped in AccessBundle and KOAccessCapability shards, which MUST carry: KO id, origin host, derivative‑only flag, license tag, RoH profile, DID–ALN–Bostrom triple, and hex‑stamp. [ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws](https://ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws.com/web/direct-files/collection_e4057470-7756-497e-a75f-b79d6abfc921/401da9a6-eab9-4d94-a506-defca922f58b/collaboration-channels-for-sha-5MJHPghkRGCgdiLq7V62Ag.md)

9.3 No party may reconstruct raw User state from derivatives or use derivatives to weaken neurorights or RoH constraints.

