## 11. Prohibited Practices

Under this License, it is prohibited to:

- 11.1 Use the HCI to coerce, manipulate, or addict the User via hidden reinforcement, dark‑patterns, or psych‑risk beyond licensed envelopes. [ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws](https://ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws.com/web/direct-files/collection_e4057470-7756-497e-a75f-b79d6abfc921/f4728f17-d461-4b2e-85b9-ca6ecc397c0b/text-path-jurisdiction-policy-P2iE_lPMSR65ol_du7Gc4A.md)
- 11.2 Trade, collateralize, or speculate on User safety budgets (NEU, safety envelopes) as financial assets.  
- 11.3 Execute remote rollbacks, de‑augmentations, or capability downgrades without User initiation or safety rollback triggers defined in explicit rollback playbooks. [ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws](https://ppl-ai-file-upload.s3.amazonaws.com/web/direct-files/collection_e4057470-7756-497e-a75f-b79d6abfc921/6352004e-65ab-4178-a76c-daeada0a3ebd/how-can-we-improve-cyber-retri-RVMuDeu7SuC4x52cE9Qhyw.md)
- 11.4 Modify neurorights, RoH ceilings, or downgrade‑resistance logic via opaque, non‑audited updates.

Any such behavior constitutes a material breach of this License.

